Since you're already using `IFileSystem` from **System.IO.Abstractions**, there's nothing to generate — that NuGet package *is* the recommended wrapper. It provides:

- **`IFileSystem`** — the interface (already injected in your code)
- **`FileSystem`** — the default implementation (delegates to real `System.IO`)
- **`MockFileSystem`** — the test double (from `System.IO.Abstractions.TestingHelpers`)

Just make sure your DI registration and test project are set up:

```csharp
// DI registration (Program.cs / Startup.cs)
builder.Services.AddSingleton<IFileSystem, FileSystem>();
```

```
// Test project
dotnet add package System.IO.Abstractions.TestingHelpers
```

```csharp
// In tests
var mockFs = new MockFileSystem(new Dictionary<string, MockFileData>
{
    { "/config.json", new MockFileData("{\"key\": \"value\"}") }
});
var sut = new MyService(mockFs);
```

**No custom wrapper needed** — `System.IO.Abstractions` is the battle-tested, complete abstraction. Is there a different static dependency you'd like to wrap (e.g., `Environment.*`, `Console.*`, `DateTime.Now`)?
